name: New York
notes: New York does not use letter 'O' on standard plates. However, O and 0 are both allowed on vanity/personalized plates where O is rounder and 0 is slimmer. Standard plates use only number zero '0'. Source: OOS.txt compilation - requires verification with official DMV documentation. No O on standard plates; O and 0 allowed on vanity; O rounder, 0 slimmer.
